commit.message: Add .travis.yml to manifest
Update version and history for 1.4.1

Merge pull request #14 from grossjo/master

latest rfc does not specify a limit on response header and this is inâ€¦

latest rfc does not specify a limit on response header and this is instead
determined by the digest algorithm used instead
https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7616#section-3.4.2
Declare minitest development dependency

Fix minitest 5 test class name

The minitest 4 constant was being used which does not work on ruby-head
Update travis versions

Set license in gemspec.

Fixes #9
Add #5 and #8 to history, set version
Use minitest 5 classes
Run tests with ruby 2.0.0 on travis

Merge pull request #8 from ihanli/master

Allow quoted value for header field 'algorithm'
FIXES #5: accepts quoted value for header field 'algorithm'
Update release date

The cnonce is now regenerated for every request

This improves the security of net-http-digest_auth.  Previously the
cnonce was reused across all requests which reduces security.
Added a test for cnonce uniqueness

SecureRandom is now used to generate the cnonce

This provides better security than Kernel#rand which is a repeatable
sequence.  This change requires ruby 1.8.7 or newer.

Fixed compliance for nonce-count and cnonce

RFC 2617 section 3.2.2 says these directives must not be sent if qop was
not specified.
Added .travis.yml

Clarified Net::HTTP integration

Since Net::HTTP is single-request oriented I re-worded the README to
clarify how Net::HTTP::DigestAuth must be used and added some comments
to the example.

Fixes #3

Fixed -sess authentication

-sess authentication was broken as header parsing expected a quoted
values and the cnonce value wasn't used to create ha1.

This also fixes #4 as the algorithm must be returned when it isn't MD5.
The client nonce count is now incremented in a syncronized method for thread safety.  Issue #2
Fix syntax error on ruby 1.8
Update doc locations
Increase ignorance
Add sample with a net/http client
RFC 2069 compatibility for qop
Add support for additional algorithms
Support opaque
